===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[caelibatus]]''', perfect passive participle of '''[[caelibare]]''', from '''[[caelebs]]''', ''[[unmarried]]''

===Noun===
'''celibacy''' (uncountable)

# state of not being married.  Sometimes confused with ''[[chastity]]'' (purity) and sexual ''[[abstinence]]'' (abstaining from sexual relations).  Members of religious communities sometimes take [[vow]]s to remain [[celibate]], since the community is their family.

